<h4><a name="Quarterly_Security_Bulletins"></a>
Security Bulletins</h4>
<h4>Account Sharing</h4>
Users should keep in mind&nbsp; that account sharing is not permitted
and they are liable for all activity on their account.
&nbsp;The&nbsp;practice of account sharing is forbidden by both BSICS
and UCI computing&nbsp;use
policies. &nbsp;Account sharing and related pranks have&nbsp; in the
past led
to&nbsp;disciplinary
action against students. &nbsp;Computing support conducts regular
audits of logs and will follow up on any suspicious account sharing
activity.<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
<h4>Computing and Network Use
Policies:</h4>
All users should be familiar with BSICS and UCI computing and network
policies. &nbsp;More information and links to each set of policies
are
provided at the following URL:<br>
<br>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;"><a
 href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/students/policy/">http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/students/policy/</a><br>
</div>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
<h4><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>Security
Scanner</h4>
For some time now, &nbsp;NACS has been providing a tool to scan
BSICS networks for potential computing vulnerabilities. &nbsp;These
scans
are
reviewed regularly and notices are sent to owners of unmanaged hosts.
&nbsp;If you receive a notice regarding a vulnerable service,
please
respond as soon as possible. &nbsp;You will be ensuring the
safety
of the network for yourself and those around you and
preventing the possible loss of connectivity for your own computing.
&nbsp;<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
<h4>Passwords</h4>
We recommend that you change your BSICS password quarterly.
&nbsp;Please remember that it is never necessary to give out your
BSICS
computing account password. &nbsp;A BSICS computing support member
will
not ask for your password. &nbsp;Directions
for
changing your BSICS passwords are available at the following URL:<br>
<br>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;"><a
 href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/windows/password_faq.php">http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/windows/password_faq.php</a><br>
</div>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>
NOTE:</span>&nbsp; If you are
accessing this website from off campus,
you will first need to sign into the campus VPN.<br>
<br>
Restrictions on the length&nbsp;of passwords for BSICS accounts has
been
lifted from 8 to 16 characters. <br>
<h4></h4>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;"><br>
<h4><a name="Virtual_Hosting"></a>Virtual
Hosting&nbsp;</h4>
For Fall 2008 Virtual Box was installed in the&nbsp;BSICS
Instructional
Computing labs. &nbsp;Computing Support is now ready to begin
offering
virtual hosting on other BSICS computing. &nbsp;One of the key
roles
that virtual hosting can offer researchers is the capability to
physically host computing in the BSICS data center and have nearly
unfettered root access to a guest OS on that system. &nbsp;If
you are interested in using virtual machine technology in your
research or instruction please send mail <a
 href="mailto:helpdesk@ics.uci.edu">BSICS Support</a>.<br>
<br>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><br>
</h4>
<h4><a name="FacultyGrad_Web_Farm_Beta_Project"></a>Faculty/Grad
Web
Farm Beta Roll Out</h4>
Computing support is opening a web farm for faculty and grad student
beta testing.<span style="font-family: monospace;">&nbsp;These</span>
special web servers are for students and faculty to run web
applications
that utilize scripting languages like PHP, ruby, or Perl. The servers
only allow students or faculty to login to them. The servers do not use
your standard BICS home directory for security reasons. &nbsp;
&nbsp;<span style="font-family: monospace;">A message will be
sent out shortly
recruiting users for the beta test program.</span><br>
<br>
<br>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a name="Broadcom_Cluster"></a>Campus
Broadcom Cluster &nbsp;(BDUC)</h4>
NACS and BSICS have collaborated in building a joint campus cluster
from
the Broadcom donated computers. Further details can be found at:<br>
<br>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;"><a class="moz-txt-link-freetext"
 href="http://www.nacs.uci.edu/computing/broadcom/index.html">http://www.nacs.uci.edu/computing/broadcom/index.html</a><br>
</div>
<br>
Access is based on requests to&nbsp;<a class="moz-txt-link-abbreviated"
 href="mailto:bducs-request@uci.edu">bduc-request@uci.edu</a>.<br>
<br>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h4><a name="Grid_Computing_Enhancements"></a>BSICS
Grid Computing
Enhancements</h4>
This list represents the available BSICS public compute/grid clusters,
architecture, size and runtime limits:<br>
<br>
<table style="text-align: left; width: 100%;" border="1" cellpadding="2"
 cellspacing="2">
  <tbody>
