<br>
The twenty node
familyguy cluster was added last fall using equipment donated to the
campus by Broadcom. &nbsp;This quarter, &nbsp;in order to ensure a fair
distribution of cycles, we have imposed run time limits on &nbsp;these
nodes.<br>
<br>
Please use checkpointing for better fault tolerance in general, but
more so on these public clusters.<br>
<br>
More information on the BSICS Grid Computing cluster is here: <a
 href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/unix/sge.php">&nbsp;http://www.ics.uci.edu/computing/unix/sge.php</a><br>
<br>
The users manual for Sun Grid Engine is available online here:
&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.sun.com/app/docs/doc/820-0699">http://docs.sun.com/app/docs/doc/820-0699</a><br>
